article.description: Clutch free throws help FIU beat UAB 70-66 in season finale
article.headline: Clutch free throws help FIU beat UAB 70-66 in season finale
article.linkText: Clutch free throws help FIU beat UAB 70-66 in season finale
article.story: MIAMI -- Daviyon Draper scored 20 points and Dennis Mavin added 19 -- sinking a pair of free throws with four seconds remaining -- as FIU edged UAB 70-66 to wrap up the regular season on Saturday night. Despite the loss, UAB (16-15, 12-6) enters the Conference USA tournament as a No. 4 seed and claims a first-round bye. Florida International (15-16, 8-10) is in the tournament for the first time, disqualified last year by NCAA sanctions. Adrian Diaz blocked 13 shots -- an NCAA season-high -- scored 14 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for the Panthers. Kris Gulley also scored 14, including a clutch three-point play with 26 seconds remaining to give FIU the lead for good. Mavin had missed a layup coming out of a UAB timeout, FIU trailing 66-65, but Gulley snared the rebound, scored and was fouled. He hit the free throw for a 68-66 lead. Nick Norton led UAB with 17 points.
